July 17, 2026 — concurrency audit and race condition fixes (branch: fix/concurrency-and-error-handling)

- Fixed cron race: bookings.cron updateMany now re-checks status: PENDING so a booking accepted
  between findMany and updateMany is not overwritten back to EXPIRED
- Fixed state transition race: accept/reject/start/complete/cancel now use updateMany with the
  expected status in the where clause; throw ConflictException when count=0 (booking state changed
  under the caller)
- Fixed cancel TOCTOU: worker cancel penalty (applyStrike) and booking status update now both
  inside the same transaction; a count=0 on the booking update rolls back the strike too
- Fixed admin TOCTOU: assertBookingNotAlreadyStruck was called outside the transaction in
  strikeWorker and resolveNoShow; concurrent admins could both pass and create duplicate strike
  records (caught by DB unique, but surfaced as raw P2002). Check moved inside applyStrike
  which runs inside the tx, now surfaces as ConflictException
- Consolidated duplicate strike logic: extracted applyStrike() to common/utils/strike.util.ts;
  removed incrementStrikeAndSuspendIfNeeded and createStrikeRecord from AdminService and
  handleWorkerCancellationPenalty logic from BookingsService
- Fixed file-before-DB order: submitVerification and uploadCredential in workers.service now
  write files before opening the DB transaction; previously a failed write left a DB record
  pointing to a missing file

