July 21, 2026 — BRD v1.3 gap closure round 3 (branch: fix/brd-gap-closure-round3)

- Fixed agreedRate (BR-13): removed agreedRate from CreateBookingDto; bookings.service.create()
  now queries WorkerCategory.rateOverride falling back to WorkerProfile.baseRate via new
  findWorkerCategoryRate assertion; client can no longer supply or override this value
- Added category validation: booking creation now throws 422 if the worker does not offer the
  requested categoryId (findWorkerCategoryRate validates the WorkerCategory record exists)
- Added barangay validation: booking creation now throws 422 if the requested barangayId is not
  in the worker's service areas (new assertWorkerServesBarangay assertion)
- Fixed assertWorkerIsAvailable: now also checks worker user.status === ACTIVE; a suspended user
  whose WorkerProfile is VERIFIED could previously still receive booking requests
- Fixed assertNoShowWindowOpen lower bound (BKG-06/08): added guard that throws 422 if the
  report is submitted before the time window ends; previously only the upper bound (2h deadline)
  was enforced
- Replaced UpdateBookingDto PartialType with dedicated DTO (BRD 9.3): exposes only
  scheduledDate, timeWindow, notes, locationAddress; prevents client from mutating
  workerId, categoryId, barangayId, agreedRate, bookingType via PATCH /bookings/:id
- Fixed update() scheduledDate validation: assertScheduledDateIsValid is now called when
  scheduledDate is present in the update payload
- Fixed complete() totalJobsCompleted (denorm counter): wrapped IN_PROGRESS → COMPLETED
  transition in a transaction and added WorkerProfile.totalJobsCompleted { increment: 1 }
  inside the same transaction
- Fixed findOne() admin bypass: ADMIN role now queries by id only (no ownership filter);
  previously admin calls incorrectly applied the worker ownership filter
- Fixed setUserSuspension(false) (WRK-05/BR-06): removed the else branch that set
  WorkerProfile.status = VERIFIED on unsuspend; reinstateWorker() is now the only path
  that restores a worker to VERIFIED (requires explicit auditNote)
- Removed @MinDate(new Date()) from CreateBookingDto (static decorator captured module-load
  time; assertScheduledDateIsValid handles this correctly at runtime using PST arithmetic)
- Updated specs: added tests for findWorkerCategoryRate (rate from override, fallback to
  baseRate, 422 if category not found), assertWorkerServesBarangay (found, 422 if not found),
  assertNoShowWindowOpen lower bound, assertWorkerIsAvailable suspended-user case, complete()
  totalJobsCompleted increment, update() scheduledDate assertion, admin unsuspend no-op
- Test count: 262 → 273 (11 new tests)

